content: Today we will discuss some popular variants of i8.
And we will do some analysis together.
Especially, i8 has become popular among Chinese renju players recently.
Some time ago, I played a game with Li Hongbin, in the tallinn-shanghai match,
and the game was later shown to you by GM xue wen xi.
However, lots of things were unanswered that time,
and most people still do not know what to conclude about this 14th move.
Does anyone of you have a clear conclusion about this 14th move?
It is said to be black sure win.
But I personally do not know it.
So, perhaps we can make it sure all together, in this lesson.
Does anyone know black win already?
I guess silence means no, or doesnt want to say
We will the analyse it from the start.
I guess, there are different ways to start here.
